<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#333399"><b>Alrien</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399"><B>Newbie</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Joined: Jul 30, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posts: 7</FONT></td><TD valign="top"><img src="/boards/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posted: 2001-08-02 02:21&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">Mez = Mesmerizing.<BR><BR>When a mob is "mezzed" it will stand inactive for a fixed duration of time.  It won't attack, won't cast, won't run - just remain mezzed <IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif"><BR><BR>Mez breaks in two conditions:<BR><BR>1. When the mob takes any type of damage.<BR>2. When the mez spell wears off.<BR><BR>Enchanters are basically the master of mez.  It's one of their primary functions, to mez extra mobs.  Bards are a respectable 2nd, with necros a distant 3rd.<BR><BR>At higher level exp fighting, it's common that the puller pulls more than 1 mob.  It's important to account for the extra mobs and mez is the easiest way.<BR><BR>Alrien</FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#f7f5e6"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=1328"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Alrien"></a>
